data.title: Cricklade Registration District
data.text:
That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of Cricklade. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 25.3.1884 out of the parish of Clyffe Pypard. See also Table 2, notes (b) and (d).

Created 1.4.1899 from the parishes of St. Sampson and St. Mary. See also Table 2, notes (d) and (d).

Abolished 1.10.1896 and added to the parish of Latton.

Abolished 1.4.1899 and added to the parish of Cricklade.

Abolished 1.4.1899 and added to the parish of Cricklade.

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of Lydiard Tregoze. See also Table 2, note (d).

Gained the parish of Broad Town (which until 25.3.1884 formed the part of the parish of Broad Hinton) from Marlborough registration district.

Lost parts of the parishes of Lydiard Millicent and Lydiard Tregoze (which became parts of the parish of Swindon on 1.10.1928) to Swindon registration district.

Lost the parts in the parishes of Blunsdon St. Andrew and Wroughton (which until 1.4.1934 formed parts of the parishes of Cricklade and Lydiard Tregoze) and the parishes of Ashton Keynes, Braydon, Broad Town, Clyffe Pypard, Cricklade, Latton, Leigh, Lydiard Millicent, Lydiard Tregoze, Lyneham, Marston Meysey, Purton, Tockenham and Wootton Bassett, to Swindon registration district.
